Centralized version control system.
Distributed Version Control Systems.(DVCS)
In the earlier(Before 2002) we use - Patches/Archive files - Multiple person contribution for a same project.
Since 2002 - we use "Bitkeeper" for project version control and team contributions.
From 2005 onwards start using "Git" for version control.
#Git Setup:
1.URL -> https://www.git-scm.com/downloads & get download and install appropriate version.
2.Open CMD prompt -> Check version -> git --version
3.>git config --global user.name "user_name"
  >git config --global user.email "email_id"
  check the updates using->git config --global --list
------------
